Â§1 path In Windows, to get the list of all the files in a folder:
Create a .txt file.
Open it with notepad. Copy and paste the following commands:
@echo off dir %1 /s/b &gt; %~n1.txt Or, if you don&rsquo;t want the list of what&rsquo;s in the subdirectory:
@echo off dir %1 /b &gt; %~n1.txt Rename it getList.bat (&ldquo;getList&rdquo; could be anything.)
Drag the target folder to this .bat file.
